#########################################################################
# Implementation of a liquid state machine using the Nemo simulator
# 
# Implementation details for the liqud are given in:
# MAASS, W. "Real-time Computing Without Stable States: A New Framework 
# for Neural Computation Based  on perturbations." Neural Computations 14 (2002): 2531-2560.
#########################################################################

INSTALLATION:
Use cmake-gui on Ubuntu to set the NeMo-0.7.2, boost_1_55_0 and Eigen3 directories.
Generate with Unix MakeFiles then
make

then run 

./main

This will train an LSM and stack the results into a best.m matlab file (for fast loading the results into matlab).

Tested on: Ubuntu 14.04 boost_1_55_0 Eigen3 and NeMo-0.7.2
